GPU cloud solutions vs Personal AI Workstation

If you are using GPU cloud services (Amazon AWS) for 8 hours a day, 5 days a week for as little as 6 months you will spend the same money as buying your own Deep Learning Workstation. After 6 months period you will return your investment and start saving money. Your personal GPU Workstation gives you up to 2X more performance comparing to cloud services.

Unparalleled cooling performance

We understand that noise level matters for workstation you are using at home or office. Most workstations on the market are using big stock coolers that come with CPU and GPU. The fans run at a very high RPM and are quite loud. Air cooling is cheap and easy and doesn’t require special assembly knowledge. For a normal office PC air-cooling is fine, but when it comes to multi-CPU workstation computer working at the maximum load 24/7 you can expect a very loud noise level, unstable performance and overheating issues .

BIZON ZX5000 comes with the custom-built liquid cooling system including cooling for CPU and all of the 4-7x GPUs. Do not mix it up with cheap CPU liquid cooling solutions that are designed for CPU cooling only. Keep in mind that most of the noise generated by GPUs.

Air-cooled TITAN RTX or RTX 2080 Tis (top-level GPUs) are extremely hot under the heavy load.
When GPUs are overheating they will activate thermal throttling mode (90C is the "red zone" where GPU activates thermal throttling).  Thermal throttling means that the fans can no longer dissipate heat and the graphics card starts to lower down the performance to protect itself.
IMPORTANT: We have seen up to 30-60% (!) performance drop due to overheating.

ZX5000/Z8000 liquid-cooled workstation computer will keep the temperatures in the safe range of 50C–60C (vs 85-90C for air-cooled). You will get 24/7 stability, low noise, and long-life for components and get 100% performance out of the GPUs. No overheating. No thermal throttling. No performance drop.

You can find the same type of cooling system in NVIDIA DGX Station (price $50,000).
